## Plan

**Approach:** Create ONE new ledger doc, `docs/plans/dogfood/retro-ledger.md`, that inventories every retrospective performed during the etude dogfood effort and the concrete improvements each produced. It is an INVENTORY + STATUS ledger, not a new retro and not re-analysis. The crucial framing: most retros did NOT produce a standalone `retro.md` — they produced runbook-rule additions (committed) and filed beads. So the ledger covers all three forms (A standalone retro docs, B cadence/phase runbook-rule retros, C the docs-reality-drift retro that motivated shipped beads). Add one index link from `docs/plans/dogfood/README.md`. PLANNING-DOCS only: no code, no edits to the retros themselves, no new retro.

**Shape (decision):** A short intro framing the three retro forms + the standing cadence rule, then ONE section per retro record. Each record uses a consistent scannable field block satisfying AC#2: **Trigger/date/scope · Evidence refs (commits/beads/docs) · Findings · Recommended changes · Landed (with [IMPLEMENTED]/[PLANNED] tag per change) · Follow-up beads · Remaining.** Implemented-vs-planned is marked per-change inline with explicit `[IMPLEMENTED]`/`[PLANNED]` tags (AC#3); a record may mix both. A dedicated short section covers the no-retro-stage finding (AC#4). A closing "Retro cadence" note records the standing rule (retro every 3 closed tickets in an autonomous loop; outputs go to skills/formulas/repo-docs, never memory).

