**Risks:**
- Drifting from ledger into re-analysis. Mitigation: fixed per-record field block; record findings/changes as inventory, link the source retro rather than re-arguing it.
- Miscategorising a change as implemented when only the rule (not a follow-up) landed. Mitigation: per-change [IMPLEMENTED]/[PLANNED] tag traced to a specific commit or open bead.
- docs-reality guard false-positive on planned-command prose. Mitigation: never co-locate a future-phrase with a shipped command token on one line; allowlist as last resort.

